title: For Sale/Trade:  PARA ORDNANCE P18 PXT ELITE LDA (Light double action)
postcontent:
I have a like new para ordnance P18 PXT ELITE  for trade or sale.

It is in 9mm, comes with original box and 2 genuine para mags.

Capacity is 18 rounds.

Has Para's proprietary LDA, Light double action. If your familiar with it, you know how baddass it is. If not, Para refined the 1911 action, so the 1st trigger pull in double action is virtually effortless. You will not find a finer trigger pull on the gun market.

Has high visibility fiber optic sights, beavertail safety, walnut grips, and satin finish.

I recently called Para about this pistol as I had my questions from people that KNOW them, and said something sounded wierd with this one. 
 Para told me, This is a PXT P18 ELITE, It was made as an elite before they actually engraved "Elite" in the side of the slide. This would account for all the "extras" that are on this gun. You can see the factory walnut grips for the Elite, as well as the same adjustable sights and front fiber optics.
 Para was interested in getting this gun back, and offered a trade in. If I dont sell it for my asking price I will just go that route.

Take a look at what these go for HERE
http://www.gundealeronline.com/category-s/124.htm?searching=Y&sort=13&cat=124&minprice=1006&show=60

ONE issue, as it has a slight bit of holster wear as seen in the pic. If not for the wear, I would ask $100 more. The wear spot will not rust..its not that bad. I just have a mindset that every pistol I own, I want to be able to carry. I use a high end bianci holster that hits this pistol in a wierd spot, so she has to go.

I bought it just because I'm a para junky. I'm just not a fan of the 9mm. All my other paras are .45. This is as they say a "tack driver". Shoots straight as a laser. @ 200 rounds through it.

When you receive it, Im sure you will be 100% happy. This pistol is a marvel in hand, and pics do not do it justice.

If you are out of state, HERE IS HOW IT WILL GO DOWN. FFL to FFL ONLY. If you pay by check, paypal or deposit into my bank it MUST clear 100%. If it is a trade, You will send 1st, After I receive your item and inspect that it is roughly in the shape as described I will in good faith send the Para. I HAVE REFERENCES from other states to show I do this in good faith. I will draw up a contract, so that there is a good legal binding so that we ARE BOTH PROTECTED. will NOT ship to PO box. Purchaser will pay shipping (should be $10-$15)

I want to make sure EVERYONE IS SATISFIED. I try to cover all points so that we both feel good about the deal.

title: For Sale:  Freedom Munitions 9mm 115 gr. 300 Rounds
postcontent:
I use have used these through my p226 with not one issue. 
http://www.freedommunitions.com/category-s/1951.htm

FREEDOM MUNITIONS inspects all cartridge cases for defects. The Scharch Range Master machines are fully automated and cases are checked for any debris and pressure tested for any splits or cracks. Primers are removed, flash holes are cleared, and primer pockets are reamed to accept new primers.

FREEDOM MUNITIONS then washes cases in an acid wash specially designed to remove all remaining burnt powder from the flash hole and interior of the case which tumbling doesn't remove. Then cases are tumbled in a dryer for a factory look and finish.

FREEDOM MUNITIONS roll sizes all cases on our own designed machines to meet S.A.A.M.I.specification. This method is the industry standard for commercial sizing, insuring the case wall is sized down to the rim which insures new component performance.

FREEDOM MUNITIONS then loads these processed components on the same fiber optic-controlled Ammo Load machines as our premium new ammo. These are the same machines used by some of the largest manufacturers in the industry. These machines assure S.A.A.M.I. specifications for priming depth, pressure and overall cartridge length.

FREEDOM MUNITIONS "Like-New" manufacturing process with the new projectile, powder and primer assures factory ammo performance that discriminating shooters expect.

title: For Trade:  Custom ordered LES BAER
location: Down Yonder up there, Kansas, United States
postcontent:
OK according to 1 individual i am a prick because i wrote this add. If my add offends you in any way then like an adult tell me and i will change any part that offends you (unless you are a gouger then offending you makes me smile :) ) My intentions are not to offend anyone but to keep the offers to only guns that i will consider trading for! Im not trying to insult your guns and people with those guns who arnt selling or gouging people i hope understand that. Thanks to all that have emailed me to tell me i have a beutiful gun or if you just want info on it im happy to speak to other people who love 1911s like i do. That is not a waste of my time. I am not a prick but i admit i ramble and it may come off the wrong way. If it does and you tell me with respect then i am happy to change my add. Thanks a god bless! PS 400 rounds have been added to the count in last two weeks!
If you have a trade worth considering then i will send you all the pics you want. If you have the desire to waste my time then you can order your own.
Now what i have is a Concept V. This is not the ones you find stock option for 16-1700. This was a special ordered pistol directly from Les Baer with a nice wait for it to be built and much higher price tag. (i still have the receipt to prove and since i am friends with my ffl dealer my cost is 10$ over cost. So unless you have the same situation or are an FFL dealer it would most likely cost you over 100 more then what i paid. When i looked them up on Guns America for the regular version most were over 150 more then what i would get them for). If a deal is made i will gladly show the receipt upon the trade.
Ordered with Mainspring/magwell
Fiber optic front sight
Tactical mag release 
Trigger ordered  to be set to 4lbs exactly (not approximately) and more. Like i said serious trades will get answers and pics.
If you know anything about Les bear pistols then you know what craftsmanship and reliability these pistols are about. Over 4,000 rounds through this pistol (with only mitch Rosen Leather around it) and not one jam. The chamber is so tight you have to Gauge your rounds before you load em up. any reload that is swelled to much will not chamber. Normal concept V go for 16-1700. This was alot more then that. If you are freaked out by 4000 rounds down the pipe and you think this is to high of a round count then you would freak at my Springfield's with 20,000+ that aren't built half as good and still perfect rifling. Now i dont mean to sound rude but i do not want to explain every detail about what is what and why. Do your research, read reviews and do not offer me a DPMS or any AR-15. I dont care if they hold 30 round or more. I don't shoot to miss....always. I just dont want people wasting my time since i really doubt i will get rid of this pistol unless i get something i really want. Im sure many of you with quality guns have been through the same. 
Does have 10-8 Perf. grips and Nighthawk short trigger. I have the original trigger/grips and grip screws. (In pics the gun needs cleaned but you can see there is no dummy scratches) Thanks and God Bless.

title: For Sale:  Winchester Legacy 94 CC Oct 30-30 Consec Lettered
postcontent: These are, in my opinion the most sought after configuration and caliber in the Legacy line. These rifles were part of the last run of Legacy rifles manufactured at the US Repeating Arms Company in New Haven, Connecticut, where it all began. Included with the rifles are letters from the Winchester historian attesting to this fact. These rifles have consective serial numbers and I understand this to be very rare as the rifles were often shuffled at different points of assembly and different points of quality control making it almost impossible for the numbers to be consecutive

title: For Sale:  H&K HK 416 D145RS .22LR NIB – Not AR15
postcontent:
This Auction is for a brand new in box HK 416 .22LR rifle by HK (Made in Germany By Carl Walther). This is the 22lr version of the weapon the Navy Seals used to take out Osama Bin Laden.

The .22 caliber HK 416 is loaded with authentic features. From its appearance, feel, and operation, right down to the sling swivel incorporated into the stock, the 416 D145RS is a replica in every sense. Flash hider, adjustable stock, etc.

Like all the .22LR H&Ks offered by Umarex, the 416 is a dedicated .22 rimfire rifle. It is engineered and built in Germany by Carl Walther with a match grade precision barrel, upper and lower metal receivers, a retractable stock, and a machined rail interface system. The 416’s pistol grip and buttstock are authentic in that they include storage compartments for small tools or batteries.

The magazines for the .22 caliber 416 are made of high-strength polymer and are designed to make loading simple and efficient. They’re available in either a 20- or 10-round version. (This is the 20 Rd version.)

The .22 caliber HK 416 D145RS operates on a blowback system. The dust cover functions and the bolt holds open when the magazine empties. Its sights are on-rail and the rear sight is adjustable for windage and elevation. Its safety selector rotates 90 degrees from ‘On Safe’ to ‘Fire’. Take down for basic cleaning is simple—there are no loose parts. Just remove the rear receiver pin and pivot the upper receiver to open.

This rifle has the weight, feel and appearance of the AR 15 version, and you can shoot it all day long with inexpensive 22lr ammo!we will only ship to FFL. $30 shipping to lower 48 states - additional charge for HI and AK and/or insurance. Certified bank or postal check preferred - if paying with Paypal + 4%. Happy Bidding!!!

postcontent:
This is a Winchester Model 68 chambered in .22 Short, Long, and Long Rifle. This is a single shot rifle. It was produced and marketed as a "Military Type Bolt Action" and its box was labeled as such. It was produced from 1934 until 1946. Roughly 100,000 of these were manufactured. These rifles were never serial numbered. The bore is very good to excellent. This rifle retains roughly 80% blueing and the wood is in very good condition. This rifle comes with the fairly uncommon front sight hood. I have never shot this rifle.
